@dev This contract is a specialized version of the converter, which implements
 a constant conversion-rate (configurable by the owner of the converter).

@dev returns the converter type
 @return see the converter types in the the main contract doc

attributes.text:
@dev This contract is a specialized version of the converter, which implements
 a constant conversion-rate (configurable by the owner of the converter).

@dev returns the converter type
 @return see the converter types in the the main contract doc

devdoc.details: This contract is a specialized version of the converter, which implements a constant conversion-rate (configurable by the owner of the converter).

acceptAnchorOwnership().details: accepts ownership of the anchor after an ownership transfer most converters are also activated as soon as they accept the anchor ownership can only be called by the contract owner note that prior to version 28, you should use 'acceptTokenOwnership' instead

acceptOwnership().details: used by a new owner to accept an ownership transfer

addLiquidity(address[],uint256[],uint256.details: increases the pool's liquidity and mints new shares in the pool to the caller

addLiquidityCost(address[],uint256,uint2.details: given the amount of one of the reserve tokens to add liquidity of, returns the required amount of each one of the other reserve tokens since an empty pool can be funded with any list of non-zero input amounts, this function assumes that the pool is not empty (has already been funded)

params._reserveAmount: amount of the relevant reserve token
params._reserveTokenIndex: index of the relevant reserve token

returns._0: the required amount of each one of the reserve tokens

addLiquidityReturn(address[],uint256[]).details: returns the amount of pool tokens entitled for given amounts of reserve tokens since an empty pool can be funded with any list of non-zero input amounts, this function assumes that the pool is not empty (has already been funded)

returns._0: the amount of pool tokens entitled for the given amounts of reserve tokens

addReserve(address,uint32).details: defines a new reserve token for the converter can only be called by the owner while the converter is inactive

params._maxConversionFee: maximum conversion fee, represented in ppm
params._registry: address of a contract registry contract

convert(address,address,uint256,address,.details: converts a specific amount of source tokens to target tokens can only be called by the bancor network contract

params._amount: amount of tokens to convert (in units of the source token)
params._beneficiary: wallet to receive the conversion result
params._trader: address of the caller who executed the conversion

returns._0: amount of tokens received (in units of the target token)
see the converter types in the the main contract doc

isActive().details: returns true if the converter is active, false otherwise

returns._0: true if the converter is active, false otherwise

isV28OrHigher().details: checks whether or not the converter version is 28 or higher

returns._0: true, since the converter version is 28 or higher

onUpgradeComplete().details: executed by the upgrader at the end of the upgrade process to handle custom pool logic

processNetworkFees().details: calculates the accumulated network fee and transfers it to the network fee wallet

rate().details: returns the worth of the 1st reserve token in units of the 2nd reserve token

returns._0: the numerator of the rate between the 1st reserve token and the 2nd reserve token
returns._1: the denominator of the rate between the 1st reserve token and the 2nd reserve token

recentAverageRate(address).details: returns the recent average rate of 1 `_token` in the other reserve token units

params._token: token to get the rate for

returns._0: recent average rate between the reserves (numerator)
returns._1: recent average rate between the reserves (denominator)

removeLiquidity(uint256,address[],uint25.details: decreases the pool's liquidity and burns the caller's shares in the pool

params._reserveMinReturnAmounts: minimum return-amount of each reserve token

returns._0: the amount of each reserve token granted for the given amount of pool tokens

removeLiquidityReturn(uint256,address[]).details: returns the amount of each reserve token entitled for a given amount of pool tokens

returns._0: the amount of each reserve token entitled for the given amount of pool tokens

reserveBalance(address).details: returns the balance of a given reserve token

returns._0: the balance of the given reserve token

reserveBalances().details: returns the balances of both reserve tokens

returns._0: the balances of both reserve tokens

reserveTokenCount().details: returns the number of reserve tokens note that prior to version 17, you should use 'connectorTokenCount' instead

reserveTokens().details: returns the array of reserve tokens

reserveWeight(address).details: returns the reserve's weight added in version 28

restrictRegistryUpdate(bool).details: restricts the permission to update the contract-registry

params._onlyOwnerCanUpdateRegistry: indicates whether or not permission is restricted to owner only

setConversionFee(uint32).details: updates the current conversion fee can only be called by the contract owner

params._conversionFee: new conversion fee, represented in ppm

setRate(uint256,uint256).details: sets the worth of the 1st reserve token in units of the 2nd reserve token can be executed only by the owner of the converter

params.rateD: the denominator of the rate between the 1st reserve token and the 2nd reserve token
params.rateN: the numerator of the rate between the 1st reserve token and the 2nd reserve token

sourceAmountAndFee(address,address,uint2.details: returns the required amount and expected fee for converting one reserve to another

params._amount: amount of target reserve tokens desired
params._sourceToken: address of the source reserve token contract
params._targetToken: address of the target reserve token contract

returns._0: required amount in units of the source reserve token
returns._1: expected fee in units of the target reserve token

targetAmountAndFee(address,address,uint2.details: returns the expected amount and expected fee for converting one reserve to another

params._amount: amount of source reserve tokens converted
params._sourceToken: address of the source reserve token contract
params._targetToken: address of the target reserve token contract

returns._0: expected amount in units of the target reserve token
returns._1: expected fee in units of the target reserve token

token().details: deprecated since version 28, backward compatibility - use only for earlier versions

transferAnchorOwnership(address).details: transfers the anchor ownership the new owner needs to accept the transfer can only be called by the converter upgrader while the upgrader is the owner note that prior to version 28, you should use 'transferAnchorOwnership' instead

transferOwnership(address).details: allows transferring the contract ownership the new owner still needs to accept the transfer can only be called by the contract owner

transferReservesOnUpgrade(address).details: transfers reserve balances to a new converter during an upgrade can only be called by the converter upgraded which should be set at its owner

params._newConverter: address of the converter to receive the new amount

upgrade().details: upgrades the converter to the latest version can only be called by the owner note that the owner needs to call acceptOwnership on the new converter after the upgrade
